COMMIT MESSAGE FORMAT (required for netdev/net-next)
===========================================================================

net: edu_net: fix skb leak on ring-full TX path

When the RX ring is full in edu_net_xmit(), the original code returns
NETDEV_TX_OK without freeing the sk_buff, leaking the allocation.

ndo_start_xmit contract:
  - NETDEV_TX_OK  → skb must be consumed
  - NETDEV_TX_BUSY → skb must remain live (qdisc retries)

Choose the drop path: free skb, increment tx_dropped, return OK.
This avoids head-of-line blocking when the ring is temporarily full.

Detected by: CONFIG_KMEMLEAK=y + ring saturation test
